<<shopHuntDebug "options">>

:: Forest Shop Hunt Escape Eden
<<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $phase is "key">>
	Light banishes the gloom around you. You and Eden both cover your eyes. <<person2>><<He>> doesn't slow down, though. <<He>> drags you from the shop.
	<br><br>

	You hear a mournful rattle from the doorframe. As you look back, it seems like the light halts just before entering the shop. Two bright green eyes stare at you from within.
	<br><br>

	<<person1>>
	<<if $shopHunt.context is "kidnap">>
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
			Black tears drop onto the grass. "<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "simple">>. You promised." <<His>> tone is eerily neutral. "You will return."
		<<else>>
			You hear a slow clapping. "Well hunted," Gwylan's voice comes.
		<</if>>
		<<His>> eyes close, and the door slams shut. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -30>><<lllyearning>>
	<<else>>
		Eden continues dragging you along. The green eyes fade away, and the door slams shut. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -30>><<lllyearning>>
	<</if>>
<<elseif $phase is "defeatGwylan">>
	Gwylan gasps. "No! No, I'm alright, I—" <br>
	The floor shakes underneath you. <br>
	"No, don't! I can—"<br>
	<span class="green">The door to the forest shop flies open, momentarily flooding it with light and banishing the gloom.</span>
	<br><br>

	Eden sees you and marches up to you, grabbing your arm. <<person2>><<He>> looks down at Gwylan with disgust, and drags you to the entrance.
	<br><br>

	<<person1>>
	<<if $shopHunt.context is "kidnap">>
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
			"<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "simple">>." Gwylan, says softly. You look back. Black tears trail down <<his>> face. "You promised."
		<<else>>
			Gwylan unsteadily stands, and claps. "Well hunted." <<He>> chuckles.
		<</if>>
		Eden pulls you across the threshold, and the door slams shut. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -30>><<lllyearning>>
	<<else>>
		The door slams shut behind you. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -30>><<lllyearning>>
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	Light banishes the gloom around you. You and Eden both cover your eyes. <<person2>><<He>> doesn't slow down, though. <<He>> drags you from the shop.
	<br><br>

	<<person1>>
	You hear a rattle from the doorframe, like strained breathing. Gwylan emerges from the darkness, frantically inspecting the remains of the door. <<He>> rubs the frame as if <<he>> were comforting a hurt child. <<person2>><<He>> turns and glares at Eden.
	<<if $shopHunt.context is "kidnap" and $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
		"You wish to take and destroy all I hold dear," <<he>> says in an eerily calm tone. "Soon, I'll have nothing to lose. You must know how that feels, Eden."
	<<else>>
		"All you do is destroy! You wish to drag everything down to be just as ugly as you are on the inside!" <<he>> yells. "Begone!"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	Eden doesn't give any indication of having heard Gwylan.
<</if>>
<br><br>

You're dragged deeper into the forest. <<npcincr Eden dom 5>><<ggdom "Eden">>
<br><br>

<<set $daily.gwylan.cafeSkip to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.noTalk to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.locked to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.noHunt to true>>
<<endevent>><<npc Eden>><<person1>>

<<link [[Next (0:30)|Eden Caged Caught]]>><<set $phase to 0>><<pass 30>><</link>>
<br>


:: Forest Shop Hunt Escape Alone
<<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
Light floods the shop and banishes the gloom for a brief moment. You cover your eyes, but you don't stop. You run, and leave both Gwylan and Eden behind. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -15>><<npcincr Eden dom -10>><<llyearning>><<lldom "Eden">>
<br><br>

<<set $daily.gwylan.cafeSkip to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.noTalk to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.locked to true>><<set $daily.gwylan.noHunt to true>>

<<link [[Next|Forest]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment
<<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _edenName to C.npc.Eden.name_known ? "Eden" : "the <<= C.npc.Eden.title>>">>
<<if $phase is "defeatEden" or shopHuntContains(shopHuntFind("eden")).includes("player")>>
	One of the shop's lights flickers on overhead, illuminating you and <<= _edenName>>, but not the darkness beyond.
	<br><br>

	Something collides with you from behind, and drags you away. You don't see what it is, though. You can only see <<= _edenName>><<if $phase is "defeatEden">>, who struggles to <<nnpc_his "Eden">> feet<</if>>.
<<else>>
	Suddenly, a blinding light shines from somewhere else.
	<<if $shopHunt.player.hide>>
		You emerge from your hiding place.
	<</if>>
	<<if shopHuntLineOfSight("player", true).includes($shopHunt.actors.find(x => x.type === "eden").id)>>
		A spotlight from above illuminates <<= _edenName>>, and a small area around <<nnpc_him "Eden">>.
	<<else>>
		A spotlight from above illuminates <<= _edenName>> in the darkness, and a small area around <<nnpc_him "Eden">>.
	<</if>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

The shop trembles.
<br><br>

"<span class="witch">Aimless.</span>"
<br><br>

The shadows become jagged like teeth. The light appears like a maw, ready to swallow <<= _edenName>> in the center.
<br><br>

You don't dare open your own mouth. The gloom presses against your lips.
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 2]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _edenName to C.npc.Eden.name_known ? "Eden" : "the <<= C.npc.Eden.title>>">>
<<npc Eden 1>><<npc Gwylan 2>><<person1>>
Laughter echoes all around <<him>>.
<br><br>

<<Hes>> surrounded. You can't see the assailants, but you know they're there. <<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> knows too. <<He>> takes aim, and fires.
<br><br>

"<span class="witch">Every careless bullet an atrocity without reason. How can one so reliant on aim be aimless?</span>"
<br><br>

The shadows bite at <<him>>. <<He>> turns and fires again. The bullet never lands.
<br><br>

"<span class="witch">I know how many bodies you've left behind. You kill. You consume. You discard. Aimlessly.</span>"
<br><br>

More laughter echoes. The word repeats like a curse. "<span class="witch">Aimless. Aimless. Aimless.</span>"
<br><br>

<<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> shouts, and shoves the barrel of <<his>> rifle into a shadow as it strikes. <<He>> pulls the trigger. <span class="red">You hear a cry of pain, followed by something slumping over.</span>
<br><br>

<<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> grins, panting. "Got you."
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 3]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 3
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _edenName to C.npc.Eden.name_known ? "Eden" : "the <<= C.npc.Eden.title>>">>

<<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>>'s pupils shrink, and <<his>> grin fades. Something crawls into the light.
<br><br>

<span class="red">A brown fox, struck by <<his>> bullet. Blood trails behind it. It's motionless.</span>
<br><br>

"No." Eden reaches down, picking up the fox. "No!"
<br><br>

The blood washes down <<= _edenName>>'s hands. <<He>> breathes heavily, lightly shaking the fox. "No, no, this isn't what I wanted."
<br><br>

The fox isn't a fox anymore. It's a person, being held in <<= _edenName>>'s arms, but no less still and bloody. Eden jumps back in shock. A red smile is painted on the figure's neck. It flickers back and forth, between being a fox and a person.
It's head snaps into an upright position and stares at Eden. It speaks.
<br><br>

"<span class="witch">Aimless.</span>"
<br><br>

<<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> reaches for <<his>> gun, but its body extends, becoming a snake that trails up <<his>> arm. No matter how <<he>> struggles, <<he>> can't shake it off.
It wraps around <<his>> neck, becoming a fox once more and hanging limp about <<his>> shoulders. A blaring voice echoes through the darkness.
<br><br>

<b>"<span class="witch">An orphan's curse would drag to hell a spirit from on high!<br>
Ever deeper, foxbane mine, is the curse in a dead mother's eye!<br>
Unscored years since the day of sin, yet you still live this rotten lie!</span>"</b>
<br><br>

<span class="red">Strands of brown fur flutter down from above. High pitched screams, full of longing, fill the emptiness. The dead fox becomes a length of rope around <<= _edenName>>'s neck.</span>
<br><br>

The rope leads up into the darkness, which swirls. The head of a colossal, three-eyed fox screams, its tongue the rope. <<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> struggles to break free, <<his>> voice drowned out by the scream.
<br><br>

<b>"<span class="witch">Hid away in solitude, my self-made coffin-box!<br>
Oblivious to the world I left as the Elk gnaws at the locks!<br>
Faceless, fateless, restless, aimless, I shot the mother fox!</span>"</b>
<br><br>

<<link [[Next|Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 4]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Shop Hunt Eden Torment 4
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set _edenName to C.npc.Eden.name_known ? "Eden" : "the <<= C.npc.Eden.title>>">>
/* ToDo: Gwylan - account for reunion and bad end start here. */

<span class="teal">Then, suddenly, it all stops.</span> The door of the shop flies open, banishing the gloom. <<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>> stands still, panting and clutching <<his>> neck.
<br><br>

Below <<him>>, a mannequin lays with a bullet lodged in its torso.
<br><br>

<<He>> stumbles towards the door, and steps outside.<<npcincr Eden dom -20>><<llldom "Eden">>
<br><br>

<<if $shopHunt.context is "rescue">>
	Gwylan shuffles out from behind a shelf. <<person2>><<He>> smiles sadly. "I'm sorry you had to see that. One day, perhaps <<person1>><<he>> will understand. It's a path only <<he>> can walk."
	<br><br>

	<<person2>><<He>> pets your head. "The shop knows much. Remembers much. Just look at how much it remembers about you." <<He>> gestures around to the clothes all around the shop. "It remembers triumphs and troubles in equal part, and Eden has much of both."
<<else>>
	Gwylan shuffles out from behind a shelf. <<person2>><<He>> smiles sadly. "I'm sorry you had to see that. I hope you understand how terrible <<person1>><<he>> is by now." <<person2>><<He>> tuts. "You were a <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "naughty">>, but I can forgive that."
	<br><br>

	<<if $worn.neck.name is "familiar collar" and $worn.neck.cursed is 1>>
		<<He>> grabs your collar and pulls you into a kiss. <<gwylanKiss 10>>
		<br><br>
	<</if>>

	<<He>> pets your head. "The shop knows much. Remembers much. Just look at how much it remembers about you." <<He>> gestures around to the clothes all around the shop. "It remembers triumphs and troubles in equal part, and Eden has much of both."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> looks around at the damage caused by <<= _edenName.toUpperFirst()>>'s rampage, and frowns. "I may need some time to clean up." <<He>> looks back to you with another smile.
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
	"Welcome home."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<shopHuntEnd `$shopHunt.context is "rescue" ? "gwylanRescue" : "gwylanKidnap"`>>
<<earnFeat "Foxbane">>

